Description: Egypt or Israel, medium group of male adults and children standing beside low stone structure in village. Males wearing gowns, head-gear. Single-storey stone buildings in background. Adult male European, wearing military uniform and leading two horses, at right of group. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Geography: Jubi not identified in sources. Unclear whether location. Circumstances: [HUN-] PIC DOC 66. The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
